</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Another Greek inve=
ntion, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sieve_of_Eratosthenes" =
title=3D"Sieve of Eratosthenes">Sieve of Eratosthenes</a>, is still used to=
 construct lists of <span class=3D"nowrap">primes.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-pomer=
ance-sciam_16-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Prime_number#cite_note-pomerance-sciam-16"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
[</span>16<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_re=
f-mollin_17-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Prime_number#cite_note-mollin-17"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></span>
