rithm, they all must produce the same result. Primes can thus be considered=
 the "basic building blocks" of the natural numbers.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-52"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number#=
cite_note-52"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>50<span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">]</span></a></sup>
