umber#cite_note-tao-aks-138"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>135<span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
and randomized <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Las_Vegas_algorithm=
" title=3D"Las Vegas algorithm">Las Vegas algorithms</a> where the random c=
hoices made by the algorithm do not affect its final answer, such as some v=
ariations of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elliptic_curve_primal=
ity_proving" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Elliptic curve primality provin=
g">elliptic curve primality proving</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-hromkovic_134-1=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number=
#cite_note-hromkovic-134"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>132<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
When the elliptic curve method concludes that a number is prime, it provide=
s <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primality_certificate" title=3D"=
Primality certificate">primality certificate</a> that can be verified quick=
ly.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-atkin-morain_139-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number#cite_note-atkin-morain-139"><span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>136<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup>
The elliptic curve primality test is the fastest in practice of the guarant=
eed-correct primality tests, but its runtime analysis is based on <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heuristic_argument" title=3D"Heuristic ar=
gument">heuristic arguments</a> rather than rigorous proofs. The <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AKS_primality_test" title=3D"AKS primality t=
est">AKS primality test</a> has mathematically proven time complexity, but =
is slower than elliptic curve primality proving in practice.<sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-morain_140-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Prime_number#cite_note-morain-140"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</spa=
n>137<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> These methods can be u=
sed to generate large random prime numbers, by generating and testing rando=
m numbers until finding one that is prime; when doing this, a faster probab=
ilistic test can quickly eliminate most composite numbers before a guarante=
ed-correct algorithm is used to verify that the remaining numbers are prime=
.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-141" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Prime_number#cite_note-141"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</spa=
n>d<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
