<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Quantum_mechanics">Quantum =
mechanics</h3></div>
<p>Beginning with the work of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hugh=
_Lowell_Montgomery" title=3D"Hugh Lowell Montgomery">Hugh Montgomery</a> an=
d <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Freeman_Dyson" title=3D"Freeman =
Dyson">Freeman Dyson</a> in the 1970s, mathematicians and physicists have s=
peculated that the zeros of the Riemann zeta function are connected to the =
energy levels of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quantum_system" c=
lass=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Quantum system">quantum systems</a>.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-182" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Prime_number#cite_note-182"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>177<sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-183" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number#cite_n=
ote-183"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>178<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup> Prime numbers are also significant in <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quantum_information_science" title=3D"Quantum inf=
ormation science">quantum information science</a>, thanks to mathematical s=
tructures such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mutually_unbiase=
d_bases" title=3D"Mutually unbiased bases">mutually unbiased bases</a> and =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SIC-POVM" title=3D"SIC-POVM">symme=
tric informationally complete positive-operator-valued measures</a>.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-184" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Prime_number#cite_note-184"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>179<sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-185" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number#cite_n=
ote-185"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>180<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Biology">Biology</h3></div>
<p>The evolutionary strategy used by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Cicada" title=3D"Cicada">cicadas</a> of the genus <i><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magicicada" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Magicicada=
">Magicicada</a></i> makes use of prime numbers.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-186" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number#cit=
e_note-186"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>181<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup> These insects spend most of their lives as <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Larva" title=3D"Larva">grubs</a> undergro=
und. They only pupate and then emerge from their burrows after 7, 13 or 17 =
years, at which point they fly about, breed, and then die after a few weeks=
 at most. Biologists theorize that these prime-numbered breeding cycle leng=
ths have evolved in order to prevent predators from synchronizing with thes=
e cycles.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-187" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number#cite_note-187"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>182<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-188" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prim=
e_number#cite_note-188"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>183<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> In contrast, the multi-year periods be=
tween flowering in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bamboo" title=
=3D"Bamboo">bamboo</a> plants are hypothesized to be <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Smooth_number" title=3D"Smooth number">smooth numbers</a=
>, having only small prime numbers in their factorizations.<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-189" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime=
_number#cite_note-189"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>184<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Arts_and_literature">Arts a=
nd literature</h3></div>
<p>Prime numbers have influenced many artists and writers. The French <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Composer" title=3D"Composer">composer</=
a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Olivier_Messiaen" title=3D"Oliv=
ier Messiaen">Olivier Messiaen</a> used prime numbers to create ametrical m=
usic through "natural phenomena". In works such as <i><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/La_Nativit%C3%A9_du_Seigneur" title=3D"La Nativit=C3=A9=
 du Seigneur">La Nativit=C3=A9 du Seigneur</a></i> (1935) and <i><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quatre_%C3%A9tudes_de_rythme" class=3D"mw-re=
direct" title=3D"Quatre =C3=A9tudes de rythme">Quatre =C3=A9tudes de rythme=
</a></i> (1949=E2=80=931950), he simultaneously employs motifs with lengths=
 given by different prime numbers to create unpredictable rhythms: the prim=
es 41, 43, 47 and 53 appear in the third =C3=A9tude, "Neumes rythmiques". A=
ccording to Messiaen this way of composing was "inspired by the movements o=
f nature, movements of free and unequal durations".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-190"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number#=
cite_note-190"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>185<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In his science fiction novel <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Contact_(novel)" title=3D"Contact (novel)">Contact</a></i>, scientist =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Sagan" title=3D"Carl Sagan">C=
arl Sagan</a> suggested that prime factorization could be used as a means o=
f establishing two-dimensional image planes in communications with aliens, =
an idea that he had first developed informally with American astronomer <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frank_Drake" title=3D"Frank Drake">Fr=
ank Drake</a> in 1975.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-191" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number#cite_note-191"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>186<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
> In the novel <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Curious_Inci=
dent_of_the_Dog_in_the_Night-Time" title=3D"The Curious Incident of the Dog=
 in the Night-Time">The Curious Incident of the Dog in the Night-Time</a></=
i> by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mark_Haddon" title=3D"Mark H=
addon">Mark Haddon</a>, the narrator arranges the sections of the story by =
consecutive prime numbers as a way to convey the mental state of its main c=
haracter, a mathematically gifted teen with <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Asperger_syndrome" title=3D"Asperger syndrome">Asperger syndrome<=
/a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-192" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Prime_number#cite_note-192"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</=
span>187<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Prime numbers are u=
sed as a metaphor for loneliness and isolation in the <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paolo_Giordano" title=3D"Paolo Giordano">Paolo Giordano=
</a> novel <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Solitude_of_Prim=
e_Numbers_(novel)" title=3D"The Solitude of Prime Numbers (novel)">The Soli=
tude of Prime Numbers</a></i>, in which they are portrayed as "outsiders" a=
mong integers.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-193" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number#cite_note-193"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>188<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
